{{EngvarB|date=May 2016}} {{Use dmy dates|date=May 2016}} '''Education in the [[Cayman Islands]]''' is compulsory to the age of 16 and is free to all Caymanian children.<ref name=bn>[https://www.state.gov/r/pa/ei/bgn/5286.htm "Background Note: Cayman Islands"]. [[Bureau of Western Hemisphere Affairs]], [[U.S. Department of State]] (February 2008). ''This article incorporates text from this source, which is in the [[public domain]].''</ref> The literacy rate for residents over age 15 is 98%.<ref name=bn/> Public schools follow a British-style educational system.<ref name=bn/> The [[Cayman Islands Education Department]] operates 10 primary, one special education, and 3 high schools.<ref name=bn/> In addition, there is a university and a law school.<ref name=bn/> There are also numerous private schools.
